  "pages": [
    {
      "text": "Lucas walked home from school on a sunny afternoon.",
      "image": "page-01.webp",
      "bg": "#FFF9C4",
      "accent": "#F9A825",
      "audio": "page-01.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "His backpack bounced as he skipped down the dusty road.",
      "image": "page-02.webp",
      "bg": "#FFF3E0",
      "accent": "#FB8C00",
      "audio": "page-02.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Suddenly, Lucas tripped on a big rock and fell hard.",
      "image": "page-03.webp",
      "bg": "#FCE4EC",
      "accent": "#E53935",
      "audio": "page-03.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "His knee hurt and his books went flying everywhere.",
      "image": "page-04.webp",
      "bg": "#FFEBEE",
      "accent": "#C62828",
      "audio": "page-04.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Lucas sat on the ground and felt tears on his cheeks.",
      "image": "page-05.webp",
      "bg": "#F3E5F5",
      "accent": "#8E24AA",
      "audio": "page-05.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "He called out, but the other children were walking fast.",
      "image": "page-06.webp",
      "bg": "#E8EAF6",
      "accent": "#3949AB",
      "audio": "page-06.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Maria rushed past him because she wanted to get home quickly.",
      "image": "page-07.webp",
      "bg": "#E3F2FD",
      "accent": "#1E88E5",
      "audio": "page-07.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Pedro ran by too, holding his soccer ball close to his chest.",
      "image": "page-08.webp",
      "bg": "#E0F7FA",
      "accent": "#00ACC1",
      "audio": "page-08.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Lucas looked at his scraped knee and took a shaky breath.",
      "image": "page-09.webp",
      "bg": "#FFF8E1",
      "accent": "#FFB300",
      "audio": "page-09.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Then soft footsteps stopped right next to him on the road.",
      "image": "page-10.webp",
      "bg": "#E8F5E9",
      "accent": "#43A047",
      "audio": "page-10.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "A kind girl named Sofia bent down and looked at his knee.",
      "image": "page-11.webp",
      "bg": "#F1F8E9",
      "accent": "#558B2F",
      "audio": "page-11.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "She pulled a clean cloth from her bag and pressed it gently.",
      "image": "page-12.webp",
      "bg": "#E0F2F1",
      "accent": "#00897B",
      "audio": "page-12.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Sofia helped Lucas pick up all his books and papers too.",
      "image": "page-13.webp",
      "bg": "#E8F5E9",
      "accent": "#2E7D32",
      "audio": "page-13.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "She held his hand and walked slowly beside him all the way home.",
      "image": "page-14.webp",
      "bg": "#FFF3E0",
      "accent": "#E65100",
      "audio": "page-14.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Lucas smiled and told Sofia she was his very best friend.",
      "image": "page-15.webp",
      "bg": "#FFF9C4",
      "accent": "#F57F17",
      "audio": "page-15.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Helping someone who is hurt is the kindest thing you can do.",
      "image": "page-16.webp",
      "bg": "#FCE4EC",
      "accent": "#AD1457",
      "audio": "page-16.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    }
  ]
}